<%- include("partials/mpheader.ejs") %>


  <main id="main">
    <!-- ======= Frequently Asked Questions Section ======= -->
    <section id="faq" class="faq">
      <div class="container" data-aos="fade-up">

        <div class="section-header">
          <!-- <span>Frequently Asked Questions</span> -->
          <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        </div>

        <div class="row justify-content-center" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="200">
          <div class="col-lg-10">

            <div class="accordion accordion-flush" id="faqlist">

              <div class="accordion-item">
                <h3 class="accordion-header">
                  <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-content-1">
                    <i class="bi bi-question-circle question-icon"></i>
                    What is e-waste, and why is it a concern?
                  </button>
                </h3>
                <div id="faq-content-1" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqlist">
                  <div class="accordion-body">
                    Solution: E-waste, or electronic waste, refers to discarded electronic devices and appliances. It's a concern because e-waste often contains hazardous materials that can harm the environment and human health if not managed properly. The solution is responsible disposal through recycling programs to prevent these risks.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div><!-- # Faq item-->

              <div class="accordion-item">
                <h3 class="accordion-header">
                  <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-content-2">
                    <i class="bi bi-question-circle question-icon"></i>
                    What happens to my electronics when I recycle them?
                  </button>
                </h3>
                <div id="faq-content-2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqlist">
                  <div class="accordion-body">
                    When you recycle e-waste, it goes through a process that involves disassembly, component extraction, and recycling of valuable materials like metals and plastics. This reduces the environmental impact of disposal and conserves resources.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div><!-- # Faq item-->

              <div class="accordion-item">
                <h3 class="accordion-header">
                  <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-content-3">
                    <i class="bi bi-question-circle question-icon"></i>
                    Can I recycle all types of electronics?
                  </button>
                </h3>
                <div id="faq-content-3" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqlist">
                  <div class="accordion-body">
                    Most electronic devices can be recycled, including computers, smartphones, televisions, and appliances. It's important to check with your local recycling program or facility for specific guidelines on what they accept.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div><!-- # Faq item-->

              <div class="accordion-item">
                <h3 class="accordion-header">
                  <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-content-4">
                    <i class="bi bi-question-circle question-icon"></i>
                    What should I do with electronics that no longer work or are beyond repair?
                  </button>
                </h3>
                <div id="faq-content-4" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqlist">
                  <div class="accordion-body">
                    <i class="bi bi-question-circle question-icon"></i>
                    These should be recycled at a certified e-waste recycling center or program. They can safely handle the disposal and recycling of non-functional electronics.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div><!-- # Faq item-->

              <div class="accordion-item">
                <h3 class="accordion-header">
                  <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-content-5">
                    <i class="bi bi-question-circle question-icon"></i>
                    What is this website, and what is its purpose?
                  </button>
                </h3>
                <div id="faq-content-5" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqlist">
                  <div class="accordion-body">
                    This website is a platform designed to help users locate e-waste collection centers in their area. Its purpose is to facilitate the responsible disposal and recycling of electronic waste.

                  </div>
                </div>
              </div><!-- # Faq item-->

              <div class="accordion-item">
                <h3 class="accordion-header">
                  <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-content-5">
                    <i class="bi bi-question-circle question-icon"></i>
                    How do I use the website to find e-waste collection centers near me?
                  </button>
                </h3>
                <div id="faq-content-5" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqlist">
                  <div class="accordion-body">
                    Simply enter your location or zip code into the search bar on the website, and it will provide a list of nearby e-waste collection centers, along with their addresses and contact information.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div><!-- # Faq item-->

              <div class="accordion-item">
                <h3 class="accordion-header">
                  <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-content-5">
                    <i class="bi bi-question-circle question-icon"></i>
                    Are the collection centers listed on the website certified for e-waste recycling?
                  </button>
                </h3>
                <div id="faq-content-5" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqlist">
                  <div class="accordion-body">
                    Yes, we only list collection centers that are certified and compliant with e-waste recycling regulations. They are equipped to handle e-waste in an environmentally responsible manner
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div><!-- # Faq item-->

              <div class="accordion-item">
                <h3 class="accordion-header">
                  <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-content-5">
                    <i class="bi bi-question-circle question-icon"></i>
                    Is there a cost associated with dropping off e-waste at these centers?
                  </button>
                </h3>
                <div id="faq-content-5" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqlist">
                  <div class="accordion-body">
                    Some centers may charge a nominal fee for certain items, while others may offer free drop-off services. It's advisable to inquire about any potential charges when contacting the center.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div><!-- # Faq item-->

            </div>

          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section><!-- End Frequently Asked Questions Section -->

    

  </main><!-- End #main -->

  <%- include("partials/mpfooter.ejs") %>